          <msContents>
            <summary>Description of models of 5 inventions for rescuing people or precious objects from fire (parafeux), selected from the collection of machines whose models were displayed in the Salon du Louvre from 1792 to Year 8 of the Republic (1799-1800). Concludes with a copy of a testimonial dated 13 nivôse in Year 8 of the Republic (3 January 1800) from Jean Francois Bralle, engineer in chief (ingénieur en chef du Département au Bureau Central). Sewn gathering of 4 bifolia, with later pagination in pencil, 185-197, upper right recto; text block outlined in red ink, some text in red ink.</summary>
